    <h2><a class="internal-link" name="contents"></a>What's in the box?</h2>
    <figure class="right-position">
      <img src="../img/photos/kocke-glagoli.jpg" alt="Verb cubes/actions" style="height: 250px;"/>
      <figcaption>Verb cubes/actions</figcaption>

      <img src="../img/photos/kocke-predmeti.jpg" alt="Noun cubes/objects" style="height: 250px;"/>
      <figcaption>Noun cubes/objects</figcaption>
    </figure>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>6 small cubes</strong> with pictures that illustrate the most important <strong>verbs/actions</strong><br/>
        <small>(in total, 36 different pictures, which means 36 different verbs/actions)</small>;
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>6 small cubes</strong> with pictures that illustrate <strong>nouns/objects</strong> connected to 6 thematic sets:
        weather, traveling, means of transport, food and beverage, clothing and body parts<br/>
        <small>(in total, 36 different pictures, which means 36 different nouns/objects)</small>;
      </li>
      <li><strong>5 large cubes</strong> to help you learn different grammatical structures:
        <ol class="smaller">
          <li>Grammar cube<br/>
            &mdash; with this cube you will learn, consolidate and acquire the following grammatical structures:
            <ul>
              <li>✓ yes/no-questions (<i>Ja-/Nein-Fragen</i>),</li>
              <li>✓ imperative sentences (<i>Imperativ</i>),</li>
              <li>✓ wh-questions (<i>W-Fragen</i>),</li>
              <li>✓ affirmative sentences (<i>Aussagesatz</i>),</li>
              <li>✓ negation (<i>Negation</i>),</li>
              <li>✓ comparison (<i>Vergleich</i>);</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Personal pronouns cube<br/>
            &mdash; with this cube you will learn, consolidate and acquire personal pronouns
            (<i>ich</i>, <i>du</i>, <i>er</i>, <i>sie</i>, <i>es</i>; <i>wir</i>, <i>ihr</i>, <i>sie</i>) in the German language;
          </li>
          <li>Modal verbs cube<br/>
            &mdash; with this cube you will learn, consolidate and acquire modal verbs
            (<i>wollen</i>, <i>sollen</i>, <i>können</i>, <i>dürfen</i>, <i>müssen</i>, <i>mögen</i>);
          </li>
          <li>Declension cube<br/>
            &mdash; with this cube you will learn, consolidate and acquire declensions in the German language
            (1. <i>Nominativ</i>, 2. <i>Gentiv</i>, 3. <i>Dativ</i>, 4. <i>Akkusativ</i>);
          </li>
          <li>The cube with different tenses<br/>
            &mdash; with this cube you will learn, consolidate and acquire different tenses in the German language
            (<i>Präsens</i>, <i>Präteritum</i>, <i>Perfekt</i>, <i>Plusquamperfekt</i>, <i>Futur I</i>, <i>Futur II</i>);
          </li>
        </ol>
      </li>
      <li>
        Sand clock: intended for a 2.5-minute exercise or as a time-limit for performing a specific task.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <figure class="inline-position">
      <img src="../img/photos/kocka-wir.jpg"    alt="Cube, wir"    style="width: 32.5%;"/>
      <img src="../img/photos/kocka-wollen.jpg" alt="Cube, wollen" style="width: 32.5%;"/>
